b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48337.htm)  [Next](sbe48339.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n21\\. The third term includes that which springs from heat.\n\np. 596\n\nCreatures sprung from heat are included in the third term--viz. that which\nsprings from a germ--which is exhibited in the text quoted. The settled\nconclusion therefore is that the evil-doers do not go to the moon.--Here\nterminates the adhikara _n_ a of 'those who do not perform sacrifices.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 22. There is entering into similarity of being with those, there being\na reason](sbe48339.htm)\n\n"